Line 226 in `classification-pipeline.ts`:

```typescript
// TODO: Stages 8-10 (AI routing, final decision, audit trail) will be wired in future work
// For now, mark session as successful
```

**The AI stages are NOT wired into the pipeline orchestrator.**

**Current implementation:**
- ✅ Stages 1-7 execute (hard assertions → multi-label selection)
- ❌ Stage 7 correctly sets `needsAiClassification: true` (line 1814 in trace)
- ❌ But the orchestrator **stops at line 224** and never calls AI stages
- ❌ Lines 226-229: Just marks session complete and returns

**Missing wiring:**
```typescript
// These stages exist but are NOT called:
// - T035: AI routing stage (implemented)
// - T035a: AI feature extraction (implemented)
// - T035b: AI classification (implemented)  
// - T035c: Final decision (implemented)
```

**Why emails show 0.01s processing:** No OpenAI API calls are being made because the AI stages never execute, even when `needsAiClassification: true`.

**Next step:** Wire stages 8-10 into the pipeline orchestrator (after line 224) to actually execute AI classification when needed.

